0102|- [HelpText]
0103|*LIFEGAME command starts "Game of Life" invented by by John Conway
0104|*in 1970 and made popular by Martin Gardner in Scientific American.
0105|*The game is played in Survo on a rectangular finite board of cells.
0106|*By various specifications the original rules and the appearence of
0107|*the game may be modified.
0108|*Original rules: At any time some of the cells will be alive or dead.
0109|*The user determines the borders of the game board and living cells at
0110|*the beginning as follows (use /BOX for drawing border lines):
0112|*LIFEGAME  / Activate this line!
0113|*         ษอออออออออออออออออออออออออออป
0114|*         บ                           บ
0115|*         บ           ***             บ
0116|*         บ          ***              บ
0117|*         บ           ***             บ
0118|*         บ                           บ
0119|*         บ                           บ
0120|*         ศอออออออออออออออออออออออออออผ
0122|*Game of Life in Survo (continued)
0124|*Let's study a cell * surrounded by 8 others:
0126|*                       123
0127|*                       8*4
0128|*                       765
0130|*If cell * is alive and it is surrounded by 4 or more living cells,
0131|*it will die by `overcrowding'. Likewise if at most 1 of the neighbours
0132|*are alive, the cell dies by `exposure'. In other cases the cell stays
0133|*alive for the next generation.
0134|*If the cell is dead (empty), it will be born again if it has exactly
0135|*3 living neighbours.
0136|*The cells on the borders are assumed to be dead all the time.
0138|*The rules for birth and death are given by ON and OFF specifications.
0139|*Thus the original (default) setting is ON=3 OFF=0145678 .
0141|*Game of Life in Survo (continued)
0143|*Other specifications:
0144|*NMAX       gives number of generations to be produced.
0145|*WAIT       gives time between successive gemerations to be displayed.
0146|*LIFE       gives a list of characters to be used for marking living
0147|*           cells. Also shadow characters may be employed for painting
0148|*           successive generations with different colors.
0149|S           Example: LIFE=***
S   |                          136
0151|*By studying the `screen saver' sucro /LIFEGAME still more specifications
0152|*may be detected.
0153|*More information is found (in Finnish) by activating
0154|*/ELOPELI
